    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Highlight the text that you would like to tag as an "Organization." Click on
                    the toolbar or the right-click options (see images below).<image
                        placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Abc71cc87-e4c9-41e4-85c9-f5eaf96bdb8d/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_ewy_gvs_3x" align="center"/><image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Aff90e67b-0bb8-4095-8dd8-442964f625c3/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_od3_mmv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>You can select which sources to use when looking up the highlighted entity. Simply click on the tab located next to your search engine. Since youâ€™re finding an organization entity, VIAF, Wikidata, and DBPedia are probably your main priorities.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A0ac2739a-41f5-4a93-a562-f89302951446/datastream/OBJ/view"<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A4f074eb1-e3ed-48cb-899b-4d81a99e7652/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_od3_mmv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
                      
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select the database that you would like to use as a link to the organization that you have chosen to tag, or insert your own URL to a different site/database not listed.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A054a9f50-c679-44ed-b396-8999069f8945/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_hbz_nmv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>If your entry is not in the CWRC entity lookup system you have the option to
                    create your own. To do this click on <cmdname>Create New</cmdname> button at the
                    bottom of that page.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A2e182286-8595-4819-8aba-6259b1f7094e/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_hbz_nmv_tp" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>You will be prompted to choose a CWRC collection for your new entity. Your selection will be logged for future use in that collection.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ad689e84a-dab5-440f-bc64-9ec9a2529768/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_hbz_nmv_tp" align="center"/></cmd> 
                <cmd>An "Add Organization" pop-up appears, fill it out (see info) and click
                    <cmdname>OK</cmdname>.</cmd>
                <info>The only mandatory field is the "Organization Name," though there are many
                    other areas that you can fill out.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ae595f149-e830-4f48-ad2f-65795a41454b/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_ozw_pmv_tp" align="center"/></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you have created an organization entry in the CWRC entity repository, you
                    can now add more information about the tag (precision, etc). Click on
                        <cmdname>Save</cmdname>.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>You have now created a new CWRC entity entry, you can use this creation the next
            time that you go to tag this entry.<image placement="break"
            
